thread.title: Celebrity Superlatives: Swift, Jagger rock

title: Celebrity Superlatives: Swift, Jagger rock
text:
Taylor Swift performs onstage with Mick Jagger during The 1989 World Tour live in Nashville September 26, 2015. (Photo: John Shearer/LP5, Getty Images for TAS)
CONNECT TWEET LINKEDIN COMMENT EMAIL MORE We dig through the latest celebrity news for highlights ... and lowlights. Think high school yearbook superlatives â€” if George Clooney and Taylor Swift were classmates.
Most rocking duet: Taylor Swift and Mick Jagger
Jagger and Swift had a major jam sesh to "(I Can't Get No) Satisfaction" while sporting matching leather ensembles on Swift's 1989 World Tour. The Rolling Stones vocalist was the latest in a string of celebrity guests on the tour: talents ranging from from Steven Tyler to Alison Krauss have graced Swift's stage in past performances.
Michelle and Barack Obama await the arrival of Chinese President Xi Jinping at the White House September 25, 2015. (Photo: Jim Watson, AFP/Getty Images)
Most stylin' First Lady: Michelle Obama
The guest of honor at the White House's state dinner was Chinese President Xi Jinping, but first lady Michelle Obama definitely stole the show. In a gesture to the international nature of the event, the first lady's black gown was a creation of Chinese-American designer, Vera Wang. We'd vote Michelle any day.
The quartet of Chanels on Fox's "Scream Queens." (Photo: Steve Dietl, Fox)
Best momma homage: Billie Lourd
Among all of the plot twists and turns on Fox's new hit Scream Queens , one of the most confusing parts was Chanel #3's earmuffs. The fuzzy headpiece made an appearance in nearly every shot that featured the diva, and the story behind the accessory is shall we say... out of this world. Billie Lourd, the actress who brings the screams to the third Chanel, is the daughter of Carrie Fisher. Fisher famously played Princess Leia, the intergalactic princess famous for her cinnamon-bun hairstyle: the inspiration for Lourd's earmuffs.
Kit Harington as Jon Snow in the HBO television series "Game of Thrones." (Photo: Helen Sloan, HBO)
Biggest sigh of relief: Kit Harington
There's no more denying it: Jon Snow is very much alive and well. After a slew of frustratingly evasive responses and denials by cast and reps, we now have photographic evidence from The Daily Mail that our favorite crow will be returning for the next season of Game of Thrones. The snapshots reveal actor Kit Harington dressed in costume and talking to the director on set in Northern Ireland, where the show is often known to shoot. Breathe easy, fans.
Amal and George attend at the premiere of "Tomorrowland" on May 25, 2015 in Tokyo, Japan. (Photo: Atsushi Tomura, Getty Images)
Most envy-inducing marriage: George and Amal Clooney
Happy anniversary, Clooneys! A year after tying the knot at an intimate wedding in Venice, the couple shows no signs of wear. In fact, since the ceremony the dynamic duo have taken their respective fields by storm. It seems only yesterday that Clooney was the world's most eligible bachelor. Now he's become the "arm candy" to Amal's brains, and a strong contender for doting husband of the year.
